In addition to the standard federal and DoD procurement certifications, the SBA SBIR Policy Directive requires the collection of certain information from firms at time of award and during the award life cycle. Each firm must provide this additional certification at the time of the Phase I award and prior to final payment on the Phase I award. This certification must state that the awardee meets the size, ownership, and other requirements of the SBIR program. 

